'''''Star Wars Insider'' 55''' is the fifty-fifth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[August 7]], [[2001]]. Issue 55 was the first overseen by chief editor [[Christopher Perkins]], who had previously served the magazine as Senior Editor beginning with [[Star Wars Insider 53|issue 53]]. This issue came packaged with an exclusive [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] trading card from the [[Topps]] trading card set ''[[2001 Topps Star Wars Evolution]]''.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[Star News]]" {{C|by [[Sue Weinlein Cook]]}}
*"[[Comics Link]]" &mdash; Top 10 Reasons to Try the ''Tales'' {{C|by [[Lee Dawson]]}}
*"[[Bookshelf]]" &mdash; Serving Darth Sidious {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Gamescape]]" &mdash; Something Wicked This Way Comes {{C|by [[Jesse Decker]]}}
*"[[HoloNet (Insider)|HoloNet]]" &mdash; Surfing with StarWars.com {{C|by [[Paul Ens]]}}
*"[[Set Piece]]: Hoth Echo Base Main Hangar" {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]] & [[Chris Reiff]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; Bootlegger's Revenge? Artistic Homage {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Dear 2-1B]]"
*"[[The Last Page]]"

===Features===
*"[[Samuel L. Jackson: The Jedi Returns]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Mace Windu was ''all talk'' in Episode I. In the next film, he has the bad guys shakin' in their boots &ndash; and no one is more thrilled than Samuel Jackson.</small>
*"[[Silas Carson: Hero with a Thousand Faces]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>He plays our favorite Cerean and the galaxy's most wanted Neimoidian: Hear what the future holds for Ki-Adi-Mundi and Nute Gunray in Episode II.</small>
*"[[Remembering Brian Daley]]" {{C|by [[Michael G. Ryan]]}}
*:<small>One of the original expanded universe authors is remembered by friends and fans.</small>
*"[[Star Wars on The Muppet Show|''Star Wars'' on ''The Muppet Show'']]" {{C|by [[Tim Harrod]]}}
*:<small>''The Onion''{{'s}} funniest hack takes us back in time, when pigs loved frogs and Jim Henson ruled television.</small>
*"[[Jedi Knight Shift: Decipher Unveils a New Star Wars Trading Card Game|Jedi Knight Shift: Decipher Unveils a New ''Star Wars'' Trading Card Game]]" {{C|by [[Cory J. Herndon]]}}
*:<small>Game designer Tom Lischke explains how to conquer the galaxy and crush the enemy in Decipher's newest trading card game.</small>

